Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle of a probably Ephesian pottery transport amphora. Finger mark at neck join inside. Clay fine, micaceous, buff; cream surface. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Charinos Unpublished parallel in the Benaki collection, Alexandria Museum. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (ID.105)
